<subSubSection pageNumber="375" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="375">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">Note:</emphasis>
Although not technically a superfluous name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1755" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Callitrichaceae" genus="Callitriche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="androgyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">C. androgyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to have been intended to replace 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Callitrichaceae" genus="Callitriche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="variety" species="palustris" variety="minima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">C. palustris</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">minima</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
(equivalent to the autonymic variety) so Lansdown &amp; Jarvis typified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1755" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Callitrichaceae" genus="Callitriche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="androgyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">C. androgyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so as to make it homotypic with 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Callitrichaceae" genus="Callitriche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="375">C. palustris</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
